{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1783338551886", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-97f6e8263ff8a889", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "python3 -c \"\nimport re, html\nwith open('/tmp/paper_2607_02129.html') as f:\n    s = f.read()\ns = re.sub(r'<script.*?</script>', ' ', s, flags=re.S|re.I)\ns = re.sub(r'<style.*?</style>', ' ', s, flags=re.S|re.I)\ns = re.sub(r'<math.*?</math>', ' [MATH] ', s, flags=re.S|re.I)\ns = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', s)\ns = html.unescape(s)\ns = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', s)\nprint(s[18000:28000])\n\" 2>&1 | head -150", "description": "Extract remaining paper text"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "22272a5d-2371-4d34-9f35-b62d8dbb538c", "uuid": "b2fe45bd-8e73-4942-af2c-016caabac79d"}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-97f6e8263ff8a889", "type": "tool_result", "content": "ade substantially. We hypothesize that the phase provides reliable cues for the relative rotation between the source and microphone array, including echoes from image sources, which the model can exploit. Similar importance of phase features was observed in DNN-based speaker distance estimation with a single microphone [ 16 ] , though further experiments are needed to validate these hypotheses. Second, the personalization experiments confirm that user-specific information contributes more to accuracy improvements than environment-specific information, reflecting the variability of speech radiation patterns across individuals. Fine-tuning on user data can yield significant gains. Third, the evaluation on the real dataset from [ 3 ] further validates the generalization capability of our method and the effectiveness of pre-training on large-scale simulated data, providing a practical way to mitigate limited annotated real-world data. Finally, while our method achieves state-of-the-art results, several limitations remain. The personalization results reveal that the model still lacks strong generalization, as performance improves significantly when adapted to new users or environments. This suggests that more diverse and larger datasets are required to achieve robust generalization and higher accuracy. Overall, these findings demonstrate that leveraging STFT phase-based features within a deep neural architecture offers a promising and scalable path toward accurate and noise-robust speaker head orientation estimation. 4 Conclusion We presented a novel approach to speaker head orientation estimation that leverages phase features from the short-time Fourier transform in combination with a deep neural network. Through experiments on both simulated and real datasets, we demonstrated that this representation provides superior robustness to noise and generalization across speakers and environments compared to existing baselines. Furthermore, our results show that fine-tuning the model on even a small amount of user- or environment-specific data can significantly improve accuracy, highlighting the value of personalization in practical deployment scenarios. References [1] A. Abad, C. Segura, D. Macho, J. Hernando, and C. Nadeu (2006) Audio person tracking in a smart-room environment . In Interspeech , External Links: Document , ISSN 2958-1796 Cited by: §1 . [2] S. Adavanne, A. Politis, J. Nikunen, and T. Virtanen (2019) Sound event localization and detection of overlapping sources using convolutional recurrent neural networks . IEEE JSTSP 13 ( 1 ), pp. 34–48 . External Links: ISSN 1941-0484 , Link , Document Cited by: §2 . [3] K. Ahuja, A. Kong, M. Goel, and C. Harrison (2020) Direction-of-voice (dov) estimation for intuitive speech interaction with smart devices ecosystems . In ACM UIST , External Links: ISBN 9781450375146 , Link , Document Cited by: §1 , §1 , §1 , §3.2 , §3.4 , §3.5 , Table 3 , Table 3 . [4] A. Asperti and D. Filippini (2023) Deep learning for head pose estimation: a survey . SN Comp. Sci. 4 ( 4 ). External Links: Link , Document Cited by: §1 . [5] S. O. Ba and J.-M. Odobez (2006) A study on visual focus of attention recognition from head pose in a meeting room . In MLMI , External Links: Link , Document Cited by: §1 . [6] M. Brandner, M. Frank, and D. Rudrich (2018) DirPat - Database and Viewer of 2D/3D Directivity Patterns of Sound Sources and Receivers . In 144th AES Convention , Note: e-Brief 425 Cited by: §3.1 . [7] H. Bredin, R. Yin, J. M. Coria, G. Gelly, P. Korshunov, M. Lavechin, D. Fustes, H. Titeux, W. Bouaziz, and M.-P. Gill (2020) Pyannote.audio: neural building blocks for speaker diarization . In ICASSP , External Links: Link , Document Cited by: §2 . [8] D. Cabrera, P. J. Davis, and A. Connolly (2011-11) Long‐term horizontal vocal directivity of opera singers: effects of singing projection and acoustic environment . Journal of Voice 25 ( 6 ), pp. e291–e303 . External Links: Document Cited by: §3.1 . [9] R. C. Felsheim, A. Brendel, P. A. Naylor, and W. Kellermann (2021) Head orientation estimation from multiple microphone arrays . In EUSIPCO , Vol. . External Links: Document Cited by: §1 . [10] D. P. Kingma and J. Ba (2015) Adam: A method for stochastic optimization . In ICLR , External Links: Link Cited by: §3.2 . [11] C. Knapp and G. Carter (1976) The generalized correlation method for estimation of time delay . IEEE TASLP 24 ( 4 ), pp. 320–327 . Cited by: §1 . [12] A. Levi and H. Silverman (2010) A robust method to extract talker azimuth orientation using a large-aperture microphone array . IEEE TASLP 18 ( 2 ). External Links: Document Cited by: §1 . [13] L. McCormack, A. Politis, and V. Pulkki (2021) Rendering of source spread for arbitrary playback setups based on spatial covariance matching . In WASPAA , Cited by: §3.3 . [14] D. Mirabilii, S. J. Schlecht, and E.A.P. Habets (2021) Generating coherence-constrained multisensor signals using balanced mixing and spectrally smooth filters . JASA 149 ( 3 ), pp. 1425–1433 . Cited by: §3.3 . [15] H. Nakajima, K. Kikuchi, T. Daigo, Y. Kaneda, K. Nakadai, and Y. Hasegawa (2009) Real-time sound source orientation estimation using a 96 channel microphone array . In IEEE/RSJ IROS , External Links: ISBN 9781424438037 Cited by: §1 . [16] M. Neri, A. Politis, D.A. Krause, M. Carli, and T. Virtanen (2024) Speaker distance estimation in enclosures from single-channel audio . IEEE/ACM TASLP 32 , pp. 2242–2254 . Cited by: §3.5 . [17] T. Peer and T. Gerkmann (2022) Phase-aware deep speech enhancement: it’s all about the frame length . JASA Express Letters 2 ( 10 ). Cited by: §2 . [18] J. M. Sachar and H. F. Silverman (2004) A baseline algorithm for estimating talker orientation using acoustical data from a large-aperture microphone array . In ICASSP , Cited by: §1 . [19] R. Scheibler, E. Bezzam,